(290, 'Tillering', 'image_bank/Tillering_75.jpg', 'Tillering_75.jpg', 'Tillering Stage in Rice - Brief Description\n===========================================\n\nOverview\n--------\nTillering is an important vegetative growth stage in rice plants where multiple side shoots, called tillers, emerge from the base of the main stem.\nEach tiller can later develop into a productive stem capable of producing grain.\n\nVisual Characteristics\n----------------------\n- Multiple green shoots emerge from the lower base of the plant.\n- Rice plants appear dense and bushy.\n- Leaves are long, narrow, upright, and bright green.\n- No grain heads or panicles are visible.\n- The field usually appears thick with green vegetation.\n\nIdentification Clues\n--------------------\n- Several stems growing from one plant base.\n- Strong vegetative growth.\n- Healthy green coloration.\n- Occurs before flowering and grain development.\n\nImportance\n----------\n- Higher tiller numbers can increase grain yield potential.\n- Proper water and nutrient supply during this stage is important.\n\nAI Training Notes\n-----------------\nImportant features for AI detection:\n- Multiple shoots from a single base.\n- Dense green canopy.\n- Absence of grains or panicles.\n- Upright leaf structure.\n\nConclusion\n----------\nThe tillering stage is recognized by active vegetative growth and the formation of multiple shoots from the base of the rice plant before reproductive stages begin.', 512, 1, '2026-05-08 12:35:48.471934', '2026-05-08 12:35:49.059321', 4, 2),
